==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kaleidophone
<hw>Ka*lei"do*phone</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <ety>[Gr. <?/ beautiful + <?/ appearance, form +
<?/ sound.]</ety> <fld>(Physics.)</fld> <def>An instrument invented by
<person>Professor Wheatstone</person>, consisting of a reflecting knob
at the end of a vibrating rod or thin plate, for making visible, in the
motion of a point of light reflected from the knob, the paths or curves
corresponding with the musical notes produced by the
vibrations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kaleidoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
